FETCH CLAUSE
============

FETCH IS USED TO FETCH FIRST NUMBER OF rows OR NEXT NUMBER OR ROWS


Q)FETCH FIRST 5 ROWS

EX: SELECT * FROM EMPLOYEE FETCH FIRST 5 ROWS ONLY;


Q)FETCH 5 TH TO 10 TH RECORDS

EX: SELECT * FROM EMPLOYEE OFFSET 4 FETCH NEXT 5 ROWS ONLY;


Q)DISPLY TOP 5 HIGHEST PAID EMPLOYEES

 SELECT * FROM EMPLOYEE ORDER BY SALARY DESC FETCH FIRST 5 ROWS ONLY;

 ========
 LIMIT
 ========

 LIMIT IS ALSO USED GET THE NUMBER OF RECORDS

Q)GET 5 RECORDS 

SELECT * FROM EMPLOYEE LIMIT 5;

Q) SKIP  2 AND THEN GET 5

SELECT * FROM EMPLOYEE OFFSET 2 LIMIT 5;


============================
FLASHBACK SUPPORT IN SQL ONLY
============================

FLASHBACK IS USED TO SEE THE DATA THAT EXISTS SOME TIME BACK FOR EX: 5 MIN BACK.

EX:-

SELECT * FROM EMPLOYEE AS OF TIMESTAMP(SYSDATE-INTERVAL '5',MINUTE)

=============================
BUILT IN FUNCTIONS IN ORACLE
=============================

1.UPPER ()
----------

IT WILL CONVERT LOWER CASE LETTERS TO THE UPPER CASE.

SELECT UPPER(EMP_NAME ) FROM EMPLOYEE;

Q)Convert all employees to UPPER case

Ans) UPDATE EMPLOYEE SET EMP_NAME=LOWER(EMP_NAME)


2.LOWER ()
----------

IT WILL CONVERT UPPPER CASE LETTERS TO THE LOWER CASE.

SELECT LOWER(EMP_NAME ) FROM EMPLOYEE;

Q)Convert all employees to lower case

Ans) UPDATE EMPLOYEE SET EMP_NAME=LOWER(EMP_NAME)


3.INITCAP()
------------
converts initials into capitals

Ex: hello world =>Hello world

SELECT INITCAP(EMP_NAME) FROM EMPLOYEE


4.LENGHT()
----------
RETURNS LENGTH OF THE STRING

SELECT EMP_NAME, LENGTH(EMP_NAME) AS LENGTH FROM EMPLOYEE

5.SUBSTR()
----------
USED TO EXTRACT PART OF THE STRING 

SELECT EMP_NAME ,SUBSTR(EMP_NAME,3,2) AS SUBSTRING FROM EMPLOYEE;

IN ABOVE IT WILL START FROM 3 CHARACTER IT WILL RETURN NEXT 2 ONLY MEANS TOTAL 2.


